  "body": "Alright, so say I have a group chat active with the member list opened:\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-04-14 12-33-08](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/163370987-339f1346-5c44-49d7-86b6-a6ed6ac36d49.png)\r\n\r\nNow from here, say I want to start another chat, so I hit the \"create chat\" button:\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-04-14 12-34-02](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/163371075-52c83501-d108-4e53-9902-d70969d2dc00.png)\r\n\r\nNotice how the create chat view doesn't take the entire width. The reason it doesn't do that is because the member list was open in the previous screen. We can verify that by for example opening a 1:on:1 chat which doesn't have members:\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-04-14 12-35-09](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/163371311-45abe11f-2ca5-4764-95fc-52691f4d0643.png)\r\n\r\nThen opening up the create chat view again:\r\n\r\n![Screenshot from 2022-04-14 12-35-36](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/445106/163371394-1a7a1379-031d-4697-9bd4-2a3998c6a35c.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
